r Norman Baker","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/47091/answer","Lewes","Norman Baker","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/47091/answer/previousversion/5666","Biography information for Norman Baker","1","Home Office","Home Office","2014-04-04","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, if she will include premises in Wales in the extension of licensing hours during FIFA World Cup matches.","false","Biography information for Alun Cairns","Vale of Glamorgan","Alun Cairns","195385"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/47092","Department for International Development","false","2014-04-28","<p> </p><p>The UK ended Budget Support to the Ugandan Government following concerns about corruption last year. Our development programme continues to support poverty reduction and growth in Uganda.</p><p> </p><p>DFID is providing £16.3 million over 4 years to support an improved HIV prevention response in Uganda, which will include provision for specifically targeting Most At Risk Populations (MARPS). We also provide support through the Global Fund to Fight AIDS, TB and Malaria. We are working with other donors and the Ministry of Health in Uganda to assess the likely impact of this legislation.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p>","Hornsey and Wood Green","Lynne Featherstone","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/47092/answer",,,,,,"2014-04-28T12:00:00.00Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/47092/answer","Biography information for Baroness Featherstone","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/47092/answer",,,,,"20","International Development","International Development","2014-04-04","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for International Development, what assessment she has made of the implications of the Anti-Homosexuality Act in Uganda for the operation of UK aid in (a) the health sector and (b) other sectors in that country.","false","Biography information for Naomi Long","Belfast East","Naomi Long","195356"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/47093","Department for International Development","false","2014-04-15","<p> </p><p>DFID support international partners monitoring the disease's spread. The UK is one of the largest funders of the international agriculture research consortium, the CGIAR (Group on International Agricultural Research). The CGIAR , FAO and national partners have established a task force to track the disease spread and to develop an effective response.</p><p> </p><p>In Mozambique, where a new outbreak of TR4 was reported November 2013, all sites where the disease was found have now been isolated, the affected plants destroyed, and appropriate phytosanitary measures have been put in place to prevent the disease from spreading. A consortium of partners, including the Mozambique Department of Agriculture, the CGIAR, Stellenbosch University, FAO and National Agricultural Research and Regulatory Organisations throughout Africa is being mobilised to address the outbreak, monitor plantations and raise awareness.</p><p> </p>","Hornsey and Wood Green","Lynne Featherstone","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/47093/answer",,,,,"195326","2014-04-15T12:00:00.00Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/47093/answer","Biography information for Baroness Featherstone","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/47093/answer",,,,,"20","International Development","International Development","2014-04-04","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for International Development, what assessment the Government has made of the spread of Fusarium Wilt Tropical Race Four.","false","Biography information for Mark Tami","Alyn and Deeside","Mark Tami","195325"
