"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/47098","Department for Transport","false","2014-04-09","<p> </p><p>The annual breakdown of the costs of HS2 up to the financial year 2020/21 is published in ‘Investing in Britain's Future', published in June 2013 at the time of Spending Round 2013. The precise details of future profiles for the period beyond 2020/21 will be set at future Spending Reviews.</p><p> </p><p> </p>","Scarborough and Whitby","Mr Robert Goodwill","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/47098/answer",,,,,,"2014-04-09T12:00:00.00Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/47098/answer","Biography information for Mr Robert Goodwill","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/47098/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2014-04-04","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, what anticipated construction costs of building High Speed 2 are for each year of its construction.","false","Biography information for Dame Cheryl Gillan","Chesham and Amersham","Mrs Cheryl Gillan","195333"
