"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/46803","Scotland Office","false","2014-04-10","<p> </p><p>The Joint Ministerial Committees take place in their Plenary, Domestic and European forms on a regular basis. Dates for future meetings are subject to agreement with the devolved administrations, as are the agendas which are agreed in advance via the JMC joint secretariat.</p><p> </p>","Orkney and Shetland","Mr Alistair Carmichael","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/46803/answer",,,,,,"2014-04-10T12:00:00.00Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/46803/answer","Biography information for Mr Alistair Carmichael","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/46803/answer",,,,,"2","Scotland","Scotland","2014-04-03","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Scotland, when the next Joint Ministerial Council (a) Plenary, (b) Domestic and (c) Europe meeting will take place; and what will be discussed at each such meeting.","false","Biography information for Margaret Curran","Glasgow East","Margaret Curran","195133"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/46804","Department for Transport","false","2014-04-08","<p>The Road Traffic (New Drivers) Act 1995 requires that drivers who accumulate six or more penalty points during their probationary period will have their licences revoked. The accumulation of offences can be for any reason. The table shows the number of drivers whose licences were revoked under the New Drivers Act who committed at least one insurance offence:</p><table><tbody><tr><td><strong>Year </strong></td><td><strong> Number of licences revoked</strong></td></tr><tr><td>2010</td><td>4,372</td></tr><tr><td>2011</td><td>5,921</td></tr><tr><td>2012</td><td>5,897</td></tr><tr><td>2013</td><td>5,606</td></tr><tr><td>2014 (up to 29 March)</td><td>1,118</td></tr><tr><td><strong> Total</strong></td><td><strong> 22,914</strong></td></tr></tbody></table>","Wimbledon","Stephen Hammond","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/46804/answer",,,,,,"2014-04-08T12:00:00.00Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/46804/answer","Biography information for Stephen Hammond","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/46804/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2014-04-03","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, how many new drivers had their licences revoked as a result of insurance offences in each year since 2010.","false","Biography information for Richard Burden","Birmingham, Northfield","Richard Burden","195128"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/46805","Department for Transport","false","2014-04-08","<p> </p><p>The Government has no plans to reinstate platforms on the West Coast Main Line and has not asked for or received any official reports on their reinstatement or removal in the 1960s. It would be for Lancashire County Council to determine whether such a scheme is a local priority and this is not the case at the present time.</p>","Wimbledon","Stephen Hammond","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/46805/answer",,,,,,"2014-04-08T12:00:00.00Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/46805/answer","Biography information for Stephen Hammond","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/46805/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2014-04-03","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, what recent reports he has received on the removal of the Carnforth station platforms from the mainline; what steps he is taking towards their reinstatement; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for David Morris","Morecambe and Lunesdale","David Morris","195068"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/46806","Department for Transport","false","2014-04-08","<p> </p><p>The Senior Traffic Commissioner's Statutory Document on Local Bus Services has been published for a further period of consultation on 07 April 2014, for six weeks. The document has been revised following responses received during the first consultation. The Senior Traffic Commissioner is aware that the industry is keen for the final document to be introduced. She will review the responses to the second consultation after it closes on 19 May but at this stage can not confirm the planned date of publication.</p>","Wimbledon","Stephen Hammond","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/46806/answer",,,,,,"2014-04-08T12:00:00.00Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/46806/answer","Biography information for Stephen Hammond","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/46806/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2014-04-03","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, when he expects to publish the Senior Traffic Commissioner's Statutory Guidance on bus reliability and punctuality.","false","Biography information for Grahame Morris","Easington","Grahame M. Morris","195092"
