ata.parliament.uk/resources/46822/answer",,,,,"26","Business, Innovation and Skills","Business, Innovation and Skills","2014-04-03","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Innovation and Skills, what the total value is of funds not yet drawn down by winning bidders under the regional growth fund in each bidding round and region.","false","Biography information for Chuka Umunna","Streatham","Mr Chuka Umunna","195181"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/46823","Department for Business, Innovation and Skills","false","2014-04-09","<p>As set out in the National Audit Office report, 22% of Royal Mail shares (220.5m) were sold to priority investors. As set out in the NAO report, at the end of January, over a half of the shares remain owned by these investors. Some have sold all their shares; some sold part of their shareholding; and others have acquired more shares.</p>","Sevenoaks","Michael Fallon","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/46823/answer",,,,,,"2014-04-09T12:00:00.00Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/46823/answer","Biography information for Sir Michael Fallon","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/46823/answer",,,,,"26","Business, Innovation and Skills","Business, Innovation and Skills","2014-04-03","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Innovation and Skills, what proportion of shares in Royal Mail allocated to priority investors in its recent privatisation are still held by those investors.","false","Biography information for Chuka Umunna","Streatham","Mr Chuka Umunna","195193"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/46824","Department for Business, Innovation and Skills","false","2014-04-09","<p>The core team working on the sale of Royal Mail shares was comprised of 17 people. None of the Department's Partner organisations were involved in taking forward the initial public offering.</p>","Sevenoaks","Michael Fallon","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/46824/answer",,,,,,"2014-04-09T12:00:00.00Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/46824/answer","Biography information for Sir Michael Fallon","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/46824/answer",,,,,"26","Business, Innovation and Skills","Business, Innovation and Skills","2014-04-03","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Innovation and Skills, how many officials from (a) his Department and (b) its executive agencies and associated public bodies worked on the Royal Mail privatisation.","false","Biography information for Chuka Umunna","Streatham","Mr Chuka Umunna","195201"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/46825","Department for Business, Innovation and Skills","false","2014-04-09","<p>All investors in Royal Mail, whether individuals or institutions, have a legitimate expectation of privacy. It would not be appropriate to disclose the list of institutions that were allocated shares in the Initial Public Offering (IPO) or the names of investors that participated in the investor engagement prior to the IPO.</p>","Sevenoaks","Michael Fallon","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/46825/answer",,,,,,"2014-04-09T12:00:00.00Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/46825/answer","Biography information for Sir Michael Fallon","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/46825/answer",,,,,"26","Business, Innovation and Skills","Business, Innovation and Skills","2014-04-03","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Innovation and Skills, what the names are of (a) the 16 priority investors selected and (b) the 21 priority investors under initial consideration by the Government in the privatisation of Royal Mail.","false","Biography information for Chuka Umunna","Streatham","Mr Chuka Umunna","195210"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/46826","Department for Business, Innovation and Skills","false","2014-04-09","<p>The process of investor engagement commenced 12 months prior to the Initial Public Offering (IPO). In the initial period, Royal Mail's management met with over 60 high quality institutions to educate them about the business. During pilot fishing in early September 2013, the management team and the Government's banking advisers engaged further with a focused group of 21 well-informed and longer-term investors. Initial indications of potential demand were received from this group; this gave the Government the confidence to proceed with announcing the Intention to Float on 12<sup>th</sup> September 2013.</p><p> </p><p> </p>","Sevenoaks","Michael Fallon","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/46826/answer",,,,,,"2014-04-09T12:00:00.00Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/46826/answer","Biography information for Sir Michael Fallon","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/46826/answer",,,,,"26","Business, Innovation and Skills","Business, Innovation and Skills","2014-04-03","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Innovation and Skills, what process the Government adopted to (a) identify and (b) select priority investors in the recent Royal Mail privatisation.","false","Biography information for Chuka Umunna","Streatham","Mr Chuka Umunna","195196"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/46827","Department for Business, Innovation and Skills","false","2014-04-09","<p>The Government did not enter into any direct arrangements with investors. All institutional investors entered into agreements with the underwriting banks (the syndicate) to purchase their allocated shares at the offer price. This is standard practice and applied to all investors.</p><p> </p><p>Details of individual allocations were not disclosed because all investors in Royal Mail - whether individuals or institutions - have a legitimate expectation of privacy.</p><p> </p>","Sevenoaks","Michael Fallon","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/46827/answer",,,,,,"2014-04-09T12:00:00.00Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/46827/answer","Biography information for Sir Michael Fallon","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/46827/answer",,,,,"26","Business, Innovation and Skills","Business, Innovation and Skills","2014-04-03","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Innovation and Skills, for what reasons details of arrangements with priority investors in respect of the privatisation of Royal Mail were not published at the time of that privatisation.","false","Biography information for Chuka Umunna","Streatham","Mr Chuka Umunna","195197"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/46828","Department for Business, Innovation and Skills","false","2014-04-28","<p>No incentives were offered to priority investors.</p>","Sevenoaks","Michael Fallon","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/46828/answer",,,,,,"2014-04-28T12:00:00.00Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/46828/answer","Biography information for Sir Michael Fallon","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/46828/answer",,,,,"26","Business, Innovation and Skills","Business, Innovation and Skills","2014-04-03","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Innovation and Skills, what incentives were (a) offered to (b) accepted by priority investors in relation to Royal Mail privatisation.","false","Biography information for Chuka Umunna","Streatham","Mr Chuka Umunna","195211"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/46829","Department for Business, Innovation and Skills","false","2014-04-29","<p>I have asked chief executives of the Executive agencies to respond directly to the Hon Member.</p><p> </p><p>Until 2013, the Department for Business, Innovation and Skills did not keep a record of the age of internal apprentices. The table shows the age of both externally recruited apprentices since 2010 and ages of those apprentices embarking on the Departments' internal apprenticeship programme in 2013. The 2013 figure refers to the ages of those on the Departments' internal programme. There are no externally recruited apprentices in the 25 years or over category.</p><table><tbody><tr><td><p> </p></td><td><p>2010</p></td><td><p>2011</p></td><td><p>2012</p></td><td><p>2013</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>16 to 18</p></td><td><p>0</p></td><td><p>0</p></td><td><p>0</p></td><td><p>1</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>19 to 24</p></td><td><p>2</p></td><td><p>1</p></td><td><p>2</p></td><td><p>11</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>25 years or over</p></td><td><p>0</p></td><td><p>0</p></td><td><p>0</p></td><td><p>16</p></td></tr></tbody></table><p>The Department for Business Innovation and Skills currently has 53 apprentices. We have had 4 successful completions this year.</p><p> </p><p>16 of these 53 apprentices are under the age of 21 with a further 6 apprentices under 21 expected to join the Department later in the year.</p>","West Suffolk","Matthew Hancock","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/46829/answer","195212 - Executive Agencies.pdf","195212 - Executive Agencies.pdf","Letters from BIS' Executive Agencies (9)","Letters from BIS' Executive Agencies (9)",,"2014-04-29T12:00:00.00Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/46829/answer","Biography information for Matt Hancock","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/46829/answer",,,,,"26","Business, Innovation and Skills","Business, Innovation and Skills","2014-04-03","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Innovation and Skills, how many apprentices aged (a) 16 to 18, (b) 19 to 24 and (c) 25 years or over are employed at each of his Department's executive agencies, non-departmental public bodies and associated bodies and agencies.","false","Biography information for Chuka Umunna","Streatham","Mr Chuka Umunna","195212"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/46831","Department for Business, Innovation and Skills","false","2014-04-09","<p>Since the Initial Public Offering, my Department has had discussions with Royal Mail in our continuing role as a minority shareholder in Royal Mail.</p><p> </p><p>There has been ad hoc contact with the Global Co-ordinators primarily to help with enquiries about the IPO but no formal correspondence.</p><p> </p><p>It is not appropriate to publish correspondence relating to the above on the grounds that it relates to our shareholding or has been provided to help develop Government policy and to do so would inhibit the free and frank advice or exchange of views for the purposes of internal deliberation.</p><p> </p><p>This Department has not had discussions or corresponded with the priority investors.</p><p> </p>","Sevenoaks","Michael Fallon","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/46831/answer",,,,,,"2014-04-09T12:00:00.00Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/46831/answer","Biography information for Sir Michael Fallon","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/46831/answer",,,,,"26","Business, Innovation and Skills","Business, Innovation and Skills","2014-04-03","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Innovation and Skills, what (a) discussions and (b) correspondence has taken place between (i) his Department, (ii) Royal Mail, (iii) banks acting as bookrunners, co-ordinators and lead managers and (iv) priority investors since the privatisation of Royal Mail took place; and if he will publish any such relevant correspondence.","false","Biography information for Chuka Umunna","Streatham","Mr Chuka Umunna","195278"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/46832","Department for Business, Innovation and Skills","false","2014-04-28","<p>The Competition and Markets Authority employs no apprentices at this time.</p><p> </p><p>As a supporter of apprenticeships, the Government launched the first Civil Service Fast Track Apprenticeship Scheme in 2013.</p><p> </p><p>As at September 2013, the most recent date for which figures are available, the Civil Service Fast Track Apprenticeship Scheme had 100 18-21 year old apprentices employed in permanent posts across government on the 2-year scheme.</p>","West Suffolk","Matthew Hancock","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/46832/answer",,,,,,"2014-04-28T12:00:00.00Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/46832/answer","Biography information for Matt Hancock","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/46832/answer",,,,,"26","Business, Innovation and Skills","Business, Innovation and Skills","2014-04-03","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Innovation and Skills, how many apprentices aged (a) 16 to 18, (b) between 19 and 24 and (c) 25 years or over are employed at the Competition and Markets Authority.","false","Biography information for Chuka Umunna","Streatham","Mr Chuka Umunna","195281"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/46833","Department for Business, Innovation and Skills","false","2014-04-09","<p>No verbal or contractual agreement of any description – including future intentions for shareholdings - was made between the Government and any investor in the Royal Mail Initial Public Offering (IPO). Any suggestion that there was a “gentleman's agreement” is false.</p>","Sevenoaks","Michael Fallon","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/46833/answer",,,,,,"2014-04-09T12:00:00.00Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/46833/answer","Biography information for Sir Michael Fallon","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/46833/answer",,,,,"26","Business, Innovation and Skills","Business, Innovation and Skills","2014-04-03","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Innovation and Skills, what (a) verbal and (b) contractual agreement was made with priority investors in relation to their shareholders during the privatisation of Royal Mail.","false","Biography information for Chuka Umunna","Streatham","Mr Chuka Umunna","195293"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/46834","Department for Business, Innovation and Skills","false","2014-04-09","<p>The Department has not seen and does not hold copies of any correspondence between Lazard or the Syndicate of banks selling Royal Mail shares and the priority investors.</p>","Sevenoaks","Michael Fallon","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/46834/answer",,,,,,"2014-04-09T12:00:00.00Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/46834/answer","Biography information for Sir Michael Fallon","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/46834/answer",,,,,"26","Business, Innovation and Skills","Business, Innovation and Skills","2014-04-03","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Innovation and Skills, what correspondence there was between (a) the bank acting as financial adviser to the Government and (b) banks acting as bookrunners, co-ordinators and lead managers (i) with and (ii) on priority investors; and if he will publish any relevant correspondence.","false","Biography information for Chuka Umunna","Streatham","Mr Chuka Umunna","195282"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/46835","Department for Business, Innovation and Skills","false","2014-04-09","<p>Together with Royal Mail's management team, the Government's independent financial adviser (Lazard) and members of the banking syndicate met with the priority investors throughout the investor engagement process. The banking advisers also met with over 500 institutional investors. The purpose of this engagement was to educate investors about the business and secure indications of potential demand and valuation.</p>","Sevenoaks","Michael Fallon","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/46835/answer",,,,,,"2014-04-09T12:00:00.00Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/46835/answer","Biography information for Sir Michael Fallon","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/46835/answer",,,,,"26","Business, Innovation and Skills","Business, Innovation and Skills","2014-04-03","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Innovation and Skills, what involvement (a) the bank acting as financial adviser to the Government and (b) banks acting as bookrunners, co-ordinators and lead managers had in discussions with priority investors on the privatisation of Royal Mail.","false","Biography information for Chuka Umunna","Streatham","Mr Chuka Umunna","195294"
