"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/46850","HM Treasury","false","2014-04-08","<p>Tax-Free Childcare will be hosted on the Government Digital Service (GDS) Gov.uk website alongside other Government digital services. HM Revenue and Customs (HMRC) have overall responsibility for the implementation of these services, in partnership with National Savings and Investments (NS&amp;I) who will operate the accounts.</p><p> </p><p>The GDS are leading the Government's work to link digital inclusion into policy programmes and digital services. HMRC have directly consulted with GDS who have been involved in the design of the process and the creation of the solution for Tax-Free Childcare.</p><p> </p><p>The Government will continue to talk with a wide variety of internal and external stakeholders to ensure that Tax-Free Childcare is as simple and secure as possible for parents to access and use.</p><p> </p>","Loughborough","Nicky Morgan","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/46850/answer",,,,,"195263 ; 195265","2014-04-08T12:00:00.00Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/46850/answer","Biography information for Nicky Morgan","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/46850/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2014-04-03","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, on what systems the online account required for the new childcare proposals announced in Budget 2014 will be implemented; and who is responsible for the implementation of those proposals.","false","Biography information for Chi Onwurah","Newcastle upon Tyne Central","Chi Onwurah","195264"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/46851","HM Treasury","false","2014-04-08","<p>Tax-Free Childcare will be hosted on the Government Digital Service (GDS) Gov.uk website alongside other Government digital services. HM Revenue and Customs (HMRC) have overall responsibility for the implementation of these services, in partnership with National Savings and Investments (NS&amp;I) who will operate the accounts.</p><p> </p><p>The GDS are leading the Government's work to link digital inclusion into policy programmes and digital services. HMRC have directly consulted with GDS who have been involved in the design of the process and the creation of the solution for Tax-Free Childcare.</p><p> </p><p>The Government will continue to talk with a wide variety of internal and external stakeholders to ensure that Tax-Free Childcare is as simple and secure as possible for parents to access and use.</p><p> </p>","Loughborough","Nicky Morgan","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/46851/answer",,,,,"195263 ; 195264","2014-04-08T12:00:00.00Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/46851/answer","Biography information for Nicky Morgan","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/46851/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2014-04-03","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, what discussions he has had with the Government Digital Service on the integration of the new online childcare accounts into gov.uk.","false","Biography information for Chi Onwurah","Newcastle upon Tyne Central","Chi Onwurah","195265"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/46852","HM Treasury","false","2014-04-08","<p>Tax-Free Childcare will be hosted on the Government Digital Service (GDS) Gov.uk website alongside other Government digital services. HM Revenue and Customs (HMRC) have overall responsibility for the implementation of these services, in partnership with National Savings and Investments (NS&amp;I) who will operate the accounts.</p><p> </p><p>The GDS are leading the Government's work to link digital inclusion into policy programmes and digital services. HMRC have directly consulted with GDS who have been involved in the design of the process and the creation of the solution for Tax-Free Childcare.</p><p> </p><p>The Government will continue to talk with a wide variety of internal and external stakeholders to ensure that Tax-Free Childcare is as simple and secure as possible for parents to access and use.</p><p> </p>","Loughborough","Nicky Morgan","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/46852/answer",,,,,"195264 ; 195265","2014-04-08T12:00:00.00Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/46852/answer","Biography information for Nicky Morgan","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/46852/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2014-04-03","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, what discussions he has had with the Secretary of State for Culture, Media and Sport on the digital inclusion implications of requiring online accounts for new childcare proposals announced in Budget 2014.","false","Biography information for Chi Onwurah","Newcastle upon Tyne Central","Chi Onwurah","195263"
