"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/46951","Speaker's Committee on the Electoral Commission","false","2014-04-10","<p> </p><p>The Electoral Commission informs me that no EROs in Scotland reported not meeting standard 3 at the recent 2013 canvass. The Commission is in the process of conducting a detailed analysis of EROs' electoral registration data from the 2013 canvass, following which it will publish its final assessment of EROs' performance.</p><p> </p>","South West Devon","Mr Gary Streeter","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/46951/answer",,,,,,"2014-04-10T12:00:00.00Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/46951/answer","Biography information for Sir Gary Streeter","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/46951/answer",,,,,"36","Speaker's Committee on the Electoral Commission","Speaker's Committee on the Electoral Commission","2014-04-03","1","House of Commons","To ask the hon. Member for South West Devon, representing the Speaker's Committee on the Electoral Commission, which parliamentary constituencies in Scotland are part of local authority areas whose electoral registration officers did not reach the required performance indicators on Standard 3 in respect of electors who failed to register to vote.","false","Biography information for Margaret Curran","Glasgow East","Margaret Curran","195258"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/46952","Department for Transport","false","2014-04-28","<p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>It is not possible to determine the number of roles within the Driver and Vehicle Standards Agency (DVSA) that are responsible for (a) driver and (b) operator compliance in the bus industry, as it forms only a part of a number of roles within the Agency. However, for the financial year of 2014/15, DVSA is budgeted to provide over 38 man-years of resource on the enforcement of the bus industry, for deployment of tasks such as roadworthiness checks, visits to licensed operators and bus operator account management.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p>","Wimbledon","Stephen Hammond","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/46952/answer",,,,,,"2014-04-28T12:00:00.00Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/46952/answer","Biography information for Stephen Hammond","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/46952/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2014-04-03","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, how many officials of the Driver and Vehicle Standards Agency are responsible for (a) driver and (b) operator compliance in the bus industry.","false","Biography information for Chris Williamson","Derby North","Chris Williamson","195277"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/46953","Department for Transport","false","2014-04-09","<p> </p><p>The Department's childcare vouchers schemes are fully compliant with the Governments tax relief schemes as set out under Section 318 ITEPA 2003. Of the two nursery provision areas in Hastings and Swansea, the latter is run by a &quot;third party&quot; organisation, therefore, it is not for the Department to comment if they has access to the Government's tax relief scheme.</p>","Wimbledon","Stephen Hammond","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/46953/answer",,,,,,"2014-04-09T12:00:00.00Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/46953/answer","Biography information for Stephen Hammond","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/46953/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2014-04-03","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, pursuant to the Answer of 24 March 2014, Official Report, column 4W on nurseries, whether his Department's workplace nurseries access the Government's tax relief scheme for workplace nurseries.","false","Biography information for Lucy Powell","Manchester Central","Lucy Powell","195241"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/46954","Department for Transport","false","2014-04-09","<p> </p><p>The information requested is not collected by the Department.</p><p> </p>","Scarborough and Whitby","Mr Robert Goodwill","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/46954/answer",,,,,,"2014-04-09T12:00:00.00Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/46954/answer","Biography information for Mr Robert Goodwill","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/46954/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2014-04-03","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, what change there has been in the level of accidents attributable to congestion in each of the last 10 years.","false","Biography information for Paul Flynn","Newport West","Paul Flynn","195246"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/46955","Department for Transport","false","2014-04-08","<p> </p><p>The Department for Transport is in detailed discussions with regional councils regarding two air routes that might qualify for support through a Public Service Obligation under financial provisions announced by the Chief Secretary to the Treasury in the 2013 Spending Round last July, to maintain regional air access to London. Of these, Dundee Council is currently tendering for an airline to operate a service between Dundee Airport and London.</p><p> </p><p>The Chancellor announced in this year's Budget that support will also be made available for start-up aid for new air routes from UK regional airports. European Union aviation State aid guidelines allow for start-up aid to be provided under certain conditions to facilitate development of new routes from Member State airports which handle fewer than five million passengers per year.</p><p> </p><p>The Department for Transport is working with the Treasury to develop guidance clarifying how the Government will ordinarily expect to interpret the European Union State aid guidelines, and explain how the funding process will operate.</p>","Scarborough and Whitby","Mr Robert Goodwill","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/46955/answer",,,,,,"2014-04-08T12:00:00.00Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/46955/answer","Biography information for Mr Robert Goodwill","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/46955/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2014-04-03","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, which airports meet the eligibility criteria for the Regional Air Connectivity Fund; and how much each such airport has been awarded in each of the last 10 years.","false","Biography information for Mary Creagh","Wakefield","Mary Creagh","195220"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/46956","Department for Transport","false","2014-04-10","<p>Under the terms of the Greater London Authority Act 1999, transport in London, including the Congestion Charge scheme, is the responsibility of Transport for London and the Mayor. Therefore, the Department for Transport has not made an assessment specifically about traffic movements in London in each year since the introduction of congestion charging.</p>","Wimbledon","Stephen Hammond","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/46956/answer",,,,,,"2014-04-10T12:00:00.00Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/46956/answer","Biography information for Stephen Hammond","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/46956/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2014-04-03","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, what assessment he has made of the effects of congestion charging on traffic movements in London in each year since the introduction of such charging.","false","Biography information for Paul Flynn","Newport West","Paul Flynn","195184"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/46957","Department for Transport","false","2014-04-09","<p> </p><p>Road congestion is measured in the Department by average morning peak speeds. Estimates of average weekday morning peak speeds, on locally managed ‘A' roads in London between 2007 and 2013 are presented in the table below. The first calendar year in this series is 2007 and earlier years are not available. Over the last 6 years, average morning peak speeds in London rose by 3.8% between 2007 and 2009, remained relatively stable until 2011, before falling by 2.7% between 2011 and 2013.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p><strong>Average weekday morning peak speeds on locally managed ‘A' roads in London</strong></p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><table><tbody><tr><td><strong>Year</strong></td><td><strong>Average morning peak speeds in London *1,*2</strong></td></tr><tr><td>2007</td><td>15.9</td></tr><tr><td>2008</td><td>16.1</td></tr><tr><td>2009</td><td>16.5</td></tr><tr><td>2010</td><td>16.4</td></tr><tr><td>2011</td><td>16.5</td></tr><tr><td>2012</td><td>16.3</td></tr><tr><td>2013</td><td>16.1</td></tr></tbody></table><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>*1 Morning peak defined as 7am to 10am. School holiday periods and the month of August are excluded</p><p>*2 Average speeds are measured in both directions of the road network</p><p>Equivalent estimates for individual London boroughs can be found on the Department for Transport's website at:</p><p><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/279125/cgn0206.xls" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/279125/cgn0206.xls</a></p><p> </p><p> </p><p>The number of reported personal injury road accidents of all severities in London in the last 10 years can be found in the table below.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p><strong>Reported personal injury road accidents in London, 2003-2012</strong></p><p> </p><p> </p><table><tbody><tr><td><strong>Year</strong></td><td><strong>Accidents</strong></td></tr><tr><td>2003</td><td>31,844</td></tr><tr><td>2004</td><td>28,778</td></tr><tr><td>2005</td><td>26,812</td></tr><tr><td>2006</td><td>24,829</td></tr><tr><td>2007</td><td>23,265</td></tr><tr><td>2008</td><td>23,160</td></tr><tr><td>2009</td><td>23,279</td></tr><tr><td>2010</td><td>24,145</td></tr><tr><td>2011</td><td>24,468</td></tr><tr><td>2012</td><td>24,097</td></tr></tbody></table><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>Data for year 2013 will be available in June 2014.</p><p> </p>","Scarborough and Whitby","Mr Robert Goodwill","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/46957/answer",,,,,,"2014-04-09T12:00:00.00Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/46957/answer","Biography information for Mr Robert Goodwill","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/46957/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2014-04-03","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, what assessment he has made of trends in the levels of (a) congestion and (b) traffic accidents in London in each of the last 10 years.","false","Biography information for Paul Flynn","Newport West","Paul Flynn","195180"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/46958","Department for Transport","false","2014-04-09","<p> </p><p> </p><p>The Department's modelling and appraisal guidance contains values to be used by transport modellers for realism testing for models (WebTAG unit M2 <a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/275597/webtag-tag-unit-m2-variable-demand-modelling.pdf" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/275597/webtag-tag-unit-m2-variable-demand-modelling.pdf</a>, see paragraph 6.4.14). The guidance on fuel cost elasticity is set at a decrease of 0.3% in traffic for a 1% increase in fuel cost. This value is based on a number of independent studies of transport demand. This is the value used in the National Transport Model and published in Road Transport Forecasts 2013 (see <a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/road-transport-forecasts-2013" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/road-transport-forecasts-2013</a></p><p> </p><p>paragraphs 1.34 and 1.35 on page 14). This refers to fuel cost generally, the Department does not have estimates for petrol and diesel separately.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>The Department does not have quantified estimates of the relationship between fuel cost and accidents.</p><p> </p>","Scarborough and Whitby","Mr Robert Goodwill","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/46958/answer",,,,,,"2014-04-09T12:00:00.00Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/46958/answer","Biography information for Mr Robert Goodwill","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/46958/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2014-04-03","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, what assessment his Department has made of whether there is a correlation between the price of (a) petrol and (b) diesel and the levels of traffic accidents and car journeys in the UK.","false","Biography information for Paul Flynn","Newport West","Paul Flynn","195182"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/46959","Department for Transport","false","2014-04-09","<p> </p><p>The number of reported a) killed and b) seriously injured cyclists in London in each of the last 10 years is given in the table below.</p><p>Number of killed and seriously injured cyclists in London: 2003-2012</p><table><tbody><tr><td><strong> </strong></td><td colspan="2"><strong>number of casualties </strong><strong> </strong></td></tr><tr><td><strong>Year</strong></td><td><strong>a) Killed </strong></td><td><strong>b)Serious </strong></td></tr><tr><td>2003</td><td>19</td><td>419</td></tr><tr><td>2004</td><td>8</td><td>332</td></tr><tr><td>2005</td><td>21</td><td>351</td></tr><tr><td>2006</td><td>19</td><td>373</td></tr><tr><td>2007</td><td>15</td><td>446</td></tr><tr><td>2008</td><td>15</td><td>430</td></tr><tr><td>2009</td><td>13</td><td>420</td></tr><tr><td>2010</td><td>10</td><td>458</td></tr><tr><td>2011</td><td>16</td><td>555</td></tr><tr><td>2012</td><td>14</td><td>659</td></tr></tbody></table><p> </p><p>Data for the year 2013 will be available in June 2014.</p>","Scarborough and Whitby","Mr Robert Goodwill","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/46959/answer",,,,,,"2014-04-09T12:00:00.00Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/46959/answer","Biography information for Mr Robert Goodwill","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/46959/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2014-04-03","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, how many (a) fatal and (b) serious injuries were suffered by cyclists in London in each of the last 10 years.","false","Biography information for Paul Flynn","Newport West","Paul Flynn","195151"
